cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper explores how fanfiction communities support learning and mentoring, which is relevant to the intersection of technology and society. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper analyzes the language and writing skills of fanfiction authors and how they improve through distributed mentoring. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the role of networked publics in facilitating distributed mentoring in fanfiction communities. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper touches on the development of writing skills and the use of technology (e.g. online forums) to support this development. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper explores how fanfiction communities use technology to support distributed mentoring and learning.
